q34: IT is super and does a great job. Only one complaint:Please make sure the tech's answering the phones enter the help ticket while talking to the person who needs the help. Thanks!

I have a few concerns about services on campus. Each time I bring my tablet on campus, I get repeating messages for connecting to the network. Some times I get connected right away, some times I just keep getting the message without connecting.
When calls are routed to Bloomington for assistance and them having to send a message to IUN to assist me. I feel like I am wasting my time with the call.
My phone frequently is off line (at least every other week) and I have to make adjustments by unplugging the phone and letting it reset.

Outside of all of this - I commend the IUN team at the HELP desk for assisting and trouble shooting my problems and being available to me. I do not have any complaints about any of them.

Faculty need to have some administrator privileges for their computer (for updates etc.)

Classroom lectern computers need to have Administrator servicing/checkup on a regular basis so faculty don't have to deal with so many pop-up dialog boxes while teaching. For example, when opening documents or PowerPoints, boxes asking if I want to make this the default.

Since I started with IU three years ago, my system runs slower and the assistance of UITS colleagues and the assistance of help desk employees has negatively changed.  We have great technology at IU, but I feel at times that no one can help me utilize it.

It seems like in just the last year, the computers in offices are running a lot slower and crashing more often than in the past. Getting help from IT seems to take longer too. Now my phone calls get transferred to Bloomington and they can't help me when I'm located on a region campus. If my calls go to Bloomington when I call the help desk, I just hang up and keep trying until my call goes through to my campus for someone to help me.
Central vs. cloud services vs. hybrid.  I appreciate the calculated UITS changes.  I imagine it's difficult sharing future unknowns.

I am slightly annoyed with the system shutdown every Wednesday at 7 a.m.  Can it not be scheduled for a time more convenient for those that work earlier?  Say, 3 or 4 a.m.?  Not a huge inconvenience but it would be nice to not be inconvenienced at all.
I think its time departmental office staff get computers that are on par with those in the computer labs around campus. From touch screens etc.

Recently, the IU wifi server has been lagging terribly on my own personal devices. Sometimes it doesn't even work at all. 
The change of Canvas is very odd. It's taking awhile to adjust to. Files were in alot of different places. With a little more doodling however, I be able to work around it.
Reimbursement of printing funds should be effective in fewer than 3 business days.

I am concerned about the problems that I'd had last semester regarding my computer; IT claimed that updates had not been installing for a couple of months.  While it was supposedly fixed, there were problems multiple times that only recently appear to have been resolved.  I wish that, if there had indeed been problems, this would have been communicated and solved much sooner.  The last time, my computer had to be rebuilt, and I am unable to catalog, because the software got deleted from the last rebuild.
Thank you for all you do to help me succeed.
I have had issues connecting to IU secure in HH but most of the time it works fine. The printer in the technology lab MH is a bit slow when processing large files but overall the network works well.

The process of changing over from oncourse to canvas was in my opinion too slow.  It seems the deadline for the end of oncourse was postponed and has created confusion having to navigate between both canvas and oncourse for two semesters.
 I am overall very satisfied with the UITS, when situations occurred with professors in the classroom or during my personal visit to the office their assistance has always been professional and expedient.
